#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:1
msgid "E4182"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:3
msgid "Compiler diagnostic name: `regex_constant_ref_in_lex_is_not_supported`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:5
msgid "Regex constants are not supported in this `lexmatch` context."
msgstr "此 `lexmatch` 上下文不支持正则常量。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:7
msgid ""
"Legacy `lexmatch` can use regex constants only in limited contexts: a "
"`StringView` target with the default first-match strategy. Other "
"`lexmatch` forms, such as `with longest`, require literal regex patterns."
msgstr ""
"旧的 `lexmatch` 只能在有限上下文中使用正则常量：目标为 `StringView`，并且使用默认的首次匹配策略。其他 "
"`lexmatch` 形式（例如 `with longest`）需要使用正则字面量模式。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:12
msgid ""
"`lexmatch` is deprecated for new code. Prefer regex match expressions "
"such as `value =~ SOME_REGEX` unless you specifically need legacy lexer-"
"style behavior."
msgstr ""
"新代码中已不推荐使用 `lexmatch`。除非你确实需要旧式词法分析器风格的行为，否则请优先使用 `value =~ SOME_REGEX` "
"这类正则匹配表达式。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:16
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr "错误示例"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:18
msgid "The following example uses a regex constant in a longest-match `lexmatch`:"
msgstr "下面的示例在最长匹配的 `lexmatch` 中使用了正则常量："

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:20
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"const WORD = re\"[A-Za-z]+\"\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn match_word(input : String) -> Unit {\n"
"  lexmatch input with longest {\n"
"    (WORD, _) => ()\n"
"    _ => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:24
msgid "MoonBit will report an error."
msgstr "MoonBit 会报告一个错误。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:26
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "建议"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:28
msgid ""
"Use a literal regex pattern in that `lexmatch` case, or rewrite the code "
"with a regex match expression:"
msgstr "在该 `lexmatch` 分支中使用正则字面量模式，或者用正则匹配表达式重写代码："

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4182.md:31
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"pub fn match_word(input : String) -> Unit {\n"
"  lexmatch input with longest {\n"
"    (\"[A-Za-z]+\", _) => ()\n"
"    _ => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
